abstract: READING, Penn., Sept. 28. -- A case that is considered remarkable by medical men in this section is that of Uriah Shunk of Lebanon, Penn., who, in July last, dived into a stream of water three feet deep, and stuck in the soft sand at the bottom. abstract: Gov. PINGREE of Michigan ought to feel flattered. Perhaps, however, he regards such wide public interest as has been shown in him as merely a proper tribute to his greatness. abstract: CHICAGO, Sept. 30. -- Wheat to-day more than recovered from yesterday's tumble. The December option closed at 1 5/8 c advance. abstract: NEW ORLEANS, Sept. 30. -- There were 3 deaths from yellow fever here to-day and 24 new cases were reported. The contagion seems to be slowly spreading into all sections of the city, but up to this time the authorities have been able to carry on their work of quarantine with some success. To-day's record was noteworthy from the fact that the fever crossed the river, one case being reported from Algiers.

abstract: CHICAGO, Oct. 1. -- Wheat made a great showing of strength during the early hours of the session to-day, but gradually changed around and closed at 1/2@5/8 cents decline. Drought news was again the prominent bullish factor, but weak Liverpool cables and anxiety to realize ultimately wiped out the advance occasioned by the dry weather. Corn followed wheat, starting strong and closing weak and 1/8 cent lower. Oats declined 1/4 cent.

abstract: CHICAGO, Oct. 2. -- The bears ran the wheat market to-day, in spite of the help the bulls received from the drought. Corn was firm and advanced one-eighth to one-quarter of a cent. Oats were unchanged at the close.

abstract: CHICAGO, Oct. 14. -- The news that John D. abstract: CINCINNATI, Oct. 23. -- At Latonia today a serious accident occurred in the last race, two jockeys being hurt. abstract: CHICAGO, Oct. 25. -- Double tracks for lake boats are proposed by lake men. abstract: ORANGE, N.J., Oct. 29. -- James A. Tyng continued his winning golf to-day on the links of the Essex County Country Club. He defeated two able men, and so won the right to be one of two competitors in the final round for the big trophy of the tournament, the silver cup offered by the Essex County Club.
